Global Funds Sell Net 13.1 billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-03-21T03:47:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-21/global-funds-sell-net-13-1-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors sold a net 13.1
billion rupees ($290 million) of Indian equity  derivatives  on
March 18, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, fell 1.1 percent to 923.3 billion rupees, or 32
percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21.  Foreign investors sold a net 5.24 billion rupees of shares
in the  cash  segment on March 18, according to preliminary data
given by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
